      • setAttribute

        public void setAttribute(String mbeanNameAsString,
                         String attributeName,
                         Object value)
        Sets the value of a specific attribute of a named MBean. The MBean is identified by its object name as a String. The first time this method is called it connects to the JMX connector server. The default behavior will try to establish a connection using RMI protocol, if it fails the RO (Remote Object) protocol is used.
        Parameters:
        mbeanNameAsString - the object name of the MBean
        attributeName - the name of the attribute
        value - the new value of the attribute

      • invoke

        public void invoke(String mbeanNameAsString,
                   String operationName,
                   Object[] params)
        Invokes an operation on an MBean. The first time this method is called it connects to the JMX connector server. The default behavior will try to establish a connection using RMI protocol, if it fails the RO (Remote Object) protocol is used.
        Parameters:
        mbeanNameAsString - the object name of the MBean
        operationName - the name of the operation to invoke
        params - the array of parameters of the operation
